Use Pgen.x to generate particle_input.dat
Use N (number of particles) as follows:
	Stat. wt. = 5
	ep_s0 = 0.10,	N = 12223
	ep_S0 = 0.15,	N = 18335
	ep_S0 = 0.20,	N = 24446

Note: 	Dp in Pgen.x is the diameter of coarse-grained particle.
	Dp-CGP = Dp*(Stat wt. ^ (1/3))

particle_input.dat contains locations (x,y,z values) of particles

